      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Managed services charge per vector stored and per query. Self-hosted pays for compute and disk. The crossover point varies by workload but typically lies around 10–50M vectors at moderate query rates."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Pinecone serverless: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "~$0.033 per million read units + $0.000003 per vector written. Very cheap for sporadic workloads; expensive for high-QPS RAG serving."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Qdrant self-hosted on a 4-core/16 GB VM: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "~$0.05–0.10/hour on most clouds. Handles ~20M 1536-dim vectors in memory. Cost fixed regardless of query count."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "pgvector: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Zero additional licensing cost. Shares the existing Postgres VM. Each HNSW search adds roughly 1–5 ms per query depending on index size."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Managed vs self-hosted crossover: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "For most applications, managed is cheaper until you're running more than ~200 queries/second or storing more than ~50M vectors. Below that threshold, the engineering time to operate self-hosted exceeds the cost savings."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Migration Path"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "It's common to start on a managed service and migrate to self-hosted as scale grows. Minimise lock-in by abstracting the vector search behind a thin interface:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n\nclass VectorStore(ABC):\n    @abstractmethod\n    def upsert(self, points: list[dict]) -> None: ...\n\n    @abstractmethod\n    def search(self, vector: list[float], top_k: int, filter: dict) -> list[dict]: ...\n\nclass PineconeStore(VectorStore):\n    def __init__(self, index): self.index = index\n\n    def upsert(self, points):\n        self.index.upsert(vectors=[\n            {\"id\": p[\"id\"], \"values\": p[\"embedding\"], \"metadata\": p[\"metadata\"]}\n            for p in points\n        ])\n\n    def search(self, vector, top_k=5, filter=None):\n        res = self.index.query(vector=vector, top_k=top_k,\n                               filter=filter, include_metadata=True)\n        return [{\"text\": m.metadata[\"text\"], \"score\": m.score} for m in res.matches]\n\nclass QdrantStore(VectorStore):\n    def __init__(self, client, collection): self.client = client; self.col = collection\n\n    def upsert(self, points):\n        from qdrant_client.models import PointStruct\n        self.client.upsert(collection_name=self.col, points=[\n            PointStruct(id=p[\"id\"], vector=p[\"embedding\"], payload=p[\"metadata\"])\n            for p in points\n        ])\n\n    def search(self, vector, top_k=5, filter=None):\n        hits = self.client.search(collection_name=self.col,\n                                  query_vector=vector, limit=top_k, with_payload=True)\n        return [{\"text\": h.payload[\"text\"], \"score\": h.score} for h in hits]\n\n# Swap implementations without touching RAG logic\nstore: VectorStore = PineconeStore(pinecone_index)\n# store: VectorStore = QdrantStore(qdrant_client, \"docs\")"
          }
        ]
      },
