      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Start managed (Pinecone or Weaviate Cloud) if you need to ship in days and your vectors number in the millions. Switch to self-hosted (Qdrant on Kubernetes or pgvector on your existing Postgres) when data residency requirements demand it, per-query costs become significant, or you need sub-10ms latency from co-location. Abstract the vector store behind a single interface from day one so the migration is a configuration change rather than a refactor."
